                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-08T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 8, 1930—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>159. Following for Minister: Legation’s 316, May 8, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>Department refers to Legation’s 226, March 28, 9 a.m., paragraph 1; Legation’s
                    245, April 3, 3 p.m.; to Department’s 137, April 19, 6 p.m., paragraphs 1 and 3,
                    and Legation’s 304, May 3, 2 p.m., final paragraph (M). In view of developments
                    indicated in the above references, the Department has assumed that discussion of
                    the Department’s latest draft is confined for the present to American and
                    British officials. Department invites attention particularly to final paragraph
                    (M) of Legation’s 304. Defer action until further instructed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
